==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Constitutive
<hw>Con"sti*tu`tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Tending or assisting to constitute or compose; elemental;
essential.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An ingredient and <qex>constitutive</qex> part of every
virtue.</q> <rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having power to enact, establish, or create;
instituting; determining.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Constitutively</ent>⟦br⟧
